FBIS3-33572 "drlat038_o_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 Colombia Reportage on Official Visit by Argentina's Menem Endorses Gaviria's OAS Candidacy PA2502042494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 22 Feb 94 PA2502042494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Azucena Lievano, from the "24 Hours" newscast] [Excerpt] President Carlos Menem has taken advantage of his official two-day visit to Colombia to confirm Argentina's support for President Gaviria in his bid for the post of OAS secretary general. He even had time to speak about his heart. Argentine President Carlos Menem today gave President Gaviria a strong endorsement in his bid for the post of OAS secretary general. Menam also announced both presidents will seek the support of other countries. [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Do you think the role President Gaviria will play at the OAS, if elected secretary general, will be a good one? [Menem] He would be a good secretary general for many reasons. The OAS, under the leadership of President Gaviria, if he is indeed elected, can improve its work and performance. [end recording] Carlos Menem went on to talk about more than the OAS. The Argentine president, who has generated many controversies over family scandals in his country, confirmed not only that his heart is good, but also that it is still beating. [Begin recording] [Menem] Thank God, my heart is doing very well. [Reporter] Are you in love or not? [Menem] I thought you were asking about the clinical and medical condition of my heart. [Reporter] I am asking about both. [Menem] Well, my heart is doing fine in both senses. [end recording] [passage omitted]
